HEADWORD: Anguilla
<hw>Anguilla</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a British colony,
comprising an island in the Caribbean Sea, east of Puerto Rico, with a
total area of 91 sq km. Its population in 1996 was estimated at 10,424.
The official language is English.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fr>1</fr> <def>the type genus of the Anguillidae:
eels.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Anguilla</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anguillan</ent>⟦br⟧
